Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @yellow onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have @garlic{2%tbsp}(minced).

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Roughly chop @dill{1/2%oz} (all for 4).

Toss sweet potato and onion on a #baking sheet{} with half the @garlic powder{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), @harissa powder{3/4%tsp}. a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}, a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. (If you like things spicy, feel free to add more harissa powder.) Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium heat. Add minced onion and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and @water{1%cup} (2 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until water has absorbed and bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Turn off heat; uncover and let cool until ready to serve.

While bulgur cooks, pat @chicken breast{10%oz}(chopped) dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

While bulgur cooks, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @apricot jam{1}, @dijon mustard{2%tsp}, remaining garlic powder, @white wine vinegar{2%tsp}, a drizzle of olive oil, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Once bulgur has cooled slightly, stir in @sunflower seeds{1/2%oz} and half the @feta cheese{1/2%cup}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Stir chicken into bulgur mixture.

Fill lettuce leaves with bulgur mixture and roasted veggies. Drizzle aioli over veggies. Sprinkle with as much dill and remaining feta as you like and serve.